<p>I'm trying to publish my site and I'm having problems.</p>  <p>My normal web.config file looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;system.web&gt;   &lt;compilation targetFramework="4.5" debug="true"&gt;        ...   &lt;/compilation&gt; &lt;/system.web&gt; </code></pre>  <p>my <code>web.config.release</code> looks something like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;system.web&gt;     &lt;compilation xdt:Transform="RemoveAttributes(debug)" /&gt; &lt;/system.web&gt; </code></pre>  <p>What it should look like when published:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;system.web&gt;   &lt;compilation targetFramework="4.5"&gt;        ...   &lt;/compilation&gt; &lt;/system.web&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Unfortunately it is not removing the <code>debug</code> attribute when I publish the site.  Does any body know as to why this is happening? Pretty sure I have it set-up how it should be. Also, other transformations are working, except for this one.</p>